The paper deals with conversation understanding systems that utilize natural language interfaces, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses retrieval models and proposes a neural utterance relevance model, which falls under the category of information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR the second likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques, such as BERT fine-tuning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI the third likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a model that outperforms competitive baselines, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG), making cs.LG the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the annotation of a dataset, which falls under the category of social and information networks (SI), making cs.SI the fifth likely sub-category.
